File: A total of 920,064 tests have been conducted cumulatively of which 28,395 were conducted since the last report. JOHANNESBURG - Mpumalanga has recorded the province's first COVID-19 related death. It said the number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in South Africa has risen to 48,285. The department has reported 46 new COVID-19 related deaths, bringing the total to 998. READ: COVID-19 deaths near 1,000 The Western Cape recorded 45 new deaths and Mpumalanga one. “We extend our condolences to the loved ones of the departed and thank the healthcare workers who treated the deceased,” the department said. Over 24,000 people have recovered so far, translating to a recovery rate of 50,5 percent according to the department. READ: Government, private hospitals agree deal on COVID-19 patients The recovery rate was previously recorded as 52,8 percent. A total of 920,064 tests have been conducted cumulatively of which 28,395 were conducted since the last report. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8 am to 4 pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.